Install Visual Studio
1. Goto: https://code.visualstudio.com/
2. Download Stable Build
3. Unzip
4. Open the application

Create an account on GitHub
https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/onboarding/getting-started-with-your-github-account

Install Git as an extension in VS
1. Select Extension (Left margin)
2. Search GIT
3. Install The Git Extension Pack

In a terminal window
Start to pull your new repository at GitHub
git remote add origin https://github.com/PhyTeK/medinst.git
git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories